## Usage Examples

### Basic Component Styling

```tsx
// Using CSS variables in inline styles
<div style={{
  backgroundColor: 'var(--mms-bg-surface)',
  padding: 'var(--mms-space-md)',
  borderRadius: 'var(--mms-radius-md)',
  color: 'var(--mms-text-primary)',
}}>
  <h2 style={{
    fontSize: 'var(--mms-text-lg)',
    fontWeight: 'var(--mms-font-semibold)',
    marginBottom: 'var(--mms-space-sm)',
  }}>
    Title
  </h2>
  <p style={{ color: 'var(--mms-text-secondary)' }}>
    Description text
  </p>
</div>
```

### Status Colors with Map

```tsx
const statusColors: Record<TrainStatus, string> = {
  available: 'var(--mms-status-available)',
  'in-service': 'var(--mms-status-in-service)',
  maintenance: 'var(--mms-status-maintenance)',
};
```

### Railway Domain Classes

Pre-defined CSS classes for railway-specific styling:

```css
/* In globals.css */
.train-id {
  font-family: var(--mms-font-mono);
  font-weight: var(--mms-font-semibold);
}

.km-value {
  font-family: var(--mms-font-mono);
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
}
```

